Name: Description
Labor Force Participation Rate: The labor force participation rate represents the proportion of the population aged 16 and older that are in the labor force. Individuals who are currently employed and who are actively seeking employment (within the last four weeks) are considered to be in the labor force.

Name: Source Notes
Labor Force Participation Rate: U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates, Table S2301 (2005-2019); retrieved from https://data.census.gov/.

Name: Notes
Labor Force Participation Rate: Previously, CCC calculated the labor force participation rate for the working age population (aged 16 to 64). In December 2019, CCC adjusted this indicator to measure the labor force participation rate of the civilian population aged 16 and older, in line with reporting from the Bureau of Labor Statistics.
